    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - REMOVE - COUNTERSHAFT
        ASSEMBLY (AUXILIARY)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY (AUXILIARY)</title>
        <para>For ease of disassembly, mount the auxiliary section upright in a vise.</para>
        <para>Both countershafts are removed the same.</para>
        <para>As the countershaft strap is removed, the countershaft can fall.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To keep the auxiliary countershafts from turning, place a shop rag or equivalent between the
                auxiliary drive gear and one countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302062">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302062" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302062" filename="../figg13/g1302062.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Loosen Bolt On Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the 15/16" bolt and retainer on the output shaft. Do not remove the bolt (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302062">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the output shaft forward far enough to partially unseat the
                bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302063">Figure 63</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302063" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302063" filename="../figg13/g1302063.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Output Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Support the auxiliary countershaft while removing the auxiliary countershaft retaining
                strap.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302064">Figure 64</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302064" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302064" filename="../figg13/g1302064.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Auxiliary Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary countershaft bearing race from the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302064">Figure 64</hotlnk>)
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, secure the countershaft assemblies in a vise and remove both the front and
                rear bearings with a bearing separator and jaw pullers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302065">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302065" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302065" filename="../figg13/g1302065.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Remove Front &#38; Rear Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
